# implementation_plan.md

# SmartQR Flutter App Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the migration and development of the SmartQR application from Kotlin/Android to a cross-platform Flutter application.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Admin Login & Settings**: A dedicated screen for admin login (Email/Password) to manage data.
> - **Primary Collection**: Data will be stored exclusively in the `smartqrflutter` collection.
> - **Firebase Rules**: Restrict write access to Email/Password authenticated users only.
> - **CSV Sync**: Admin can upload and sync the `;` separated CSV file to Firestore.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Architecture
- **Framework:** Flutter (Latest Stable)
- **State Management:** Provider or Riverpod
- **Database:** Isar (Local) + Firebase Firestore (Cloud)
- **Auth:** Firebase Anonymous Auth
- **QR Engine:** `mobile_scanner` or `google_mlkit_barcode_scanning`

---

### UI Components

#### [NEW] [main_screen.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/screens/main_screen.dart)
Prioritizes the product image. Includes a manual search bar at the top and a corner button to toggle technical details.

#### [NEW] [qr_scanner_screen.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/screens/qr_scanner_screen.dart)
Mobile scanner with 1.2s dwell time. Redirects to main screen on success.

#### [NEW] [settings_screen.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart)
Admin login interface (Email/Password) and CSV sync button.

#### [NEW] [details_panel.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/widgets/details_panel.dart)
A toggleable overlay or side panel for displaying dynamic properties from the CSV.

---

### Data Layer

#### [NEW] [product_model.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/models/product_model.dart)
Flexible product model supporting dynamic properties via Map/JSON.

#### [NEW] [sync_service.dart](file:///c:/yesileee/SmartQR/lib/services/sync_service.dart)
Firebase Firestore sync logic with batch processing.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `flutter test` for unit tests on data models and sync logic.
- Run `flutter analyze` to ensure code quality.

### Manual Verification
- Verify QR scanning sensitivity and dwell time on physical devices or emulator (mocking camera if needed).
- Test CSV import functionality.
- Verify UI responsiveness across different screen sizes.
